arXiv:2212.09838v2 Announce Type: replace 
Abstract: This paper is concerned with the following parabolic-parabolic-elliptic chemotaxis system with singular sensitivity and Lotka-Volterra competitive kinetics,
   egin{equation}  egin{cases} u_t=\Delta u-\chi_1 
abla\cdot ( rac{u}{w} 
abla w)+u(a_1-b_1u-c_1v) ,\quad &x\in \Omega\cr v_t=\Delta v-\chi_2 
abla\cdot ( rac{v}{w} 
abla w)+v(a_2-b_2v-c_2u),\quad &x\in \Omega\cr 0=\Delta w-\mu w +
u u+ \lambda v,\quad &x\in \Omega \cr  rac{\partial u}{\partial n}= rac{\partial v}{\partial n}= rac{\partial w}{\partial n}=0,\quad &x\in\partial\Omega, \end{cases} \end{equation} where $\Omega \subset \mathbb{R}^N$ is a bounded smooth domain, and $\chi_i$, $a_i$, $b_i$, $ c_i$ ($i=1,2$) and $\mu,\, 
u, \, \lambda$ are positive constants. This is the first work on two-species chemotaxis-competition system with singular sensitivity and Lotka-Volterra competitive kinetics. Among others, we prove that for any given nonnegative initial data $u_0,v_0\in C^0( ar\Omega)$ with $u_0+v_0
ot \equiv 0$, (0.1) has a unique globally defined classical solution $(u(t,x;u_0,v_0),v(t,x;u_0,v_0),w(t,x;u_0,v_0))$ with $u(0,x;u_0,v_0)=u_0(x)$ and $v(0,x;u_0,v_0)=v_0(x)$ provided that $\min\{a_1,a_2\}$ is large relative to $\chi_1,\chi_2$ and $u_0+v_0$ is not small. Moreover, under the same condition, we prove that  egin{equation*}
  \limsup_{t	o\infty} \|u(t,\cdot;u_0,v_0)+v(t,\cdot;u_0,v_0)\|_\infty\le M^*, \end{equation*} and  egin{equation*}
  \liminf_{t	o\infty} \inf_{x\in\Omega}(u(t,x,u_0,v_0)+v(t,x;u_0,v_0))\ge m^*, \end{equation*} for some positive constants $M^*,m^*$ independent of $u_0,v_0$, the latter is referred to as combined pointwise persistence.
